'''Dōmo arigatō''' is a [[Japan|Japanese]] expression that translates to "Thank you." Knowledge of the expression was popularized in the Western world at least in part by the song [[Mr. Roboto]] by [[Styx]] which features the line "''Dōmo arigatō'', Mr. Roboto."

The line has been used as a pop culture reference a number of times, including in the film '[[Austin Powers in Goldmember]]', the song "The King Of Bedside Manor" by the [[Barenaked Ladies]], and cartoons [[Futurama]] and [[The Simpsons]].

